<p>####</p>
<ol>
  <li>A shell script is a computer program designed to be run by the Unix/Linux
shell which could be one of the following:
    <ul>
      <li>Bourne Shell</li>
      <li>C Shell</li>
      <li>The GNU Bourne-Again Shell</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>A shell is a command-line interpreter and typical operations performed by
shell scripts include file manipulation, program execution, and printing
text.</li>
  <li>Shell Scripts: just a list of commands</li>
</ol>

